  "texts": [
    "Although various model architectures could be employed, in this work we adopt the data-based model proposed in [31], which employs gated recurrent unit (GRU) networks within the recurrent neural network (RNN) family, due to their strong approximation capabilities and relatively simple architecture [23].The MPC controller ( 6) is implemented with the described ensemble as prediction model, horizon H = 72, and costL(h) = τ • c(h) • P 0 (h),(9)with c(h) the electricity energy cost and P 0 (h) the power supplied by the heating station, i.e., where c p is the specific water heat coefficient.",
    "Furthermore, the constraint sets are defined asP 0 (h) = c p • q 0 (h) • T s 0 (h) -T r 0 (h),(10)X = {x ∈ R nx | -1 nx ≤ x ≤ 1 nx }, U = ũ ∈ R nũ |65 ≤ T s 0 ≤ 85, -15 ≤ q TES ≤ 15, Y(h) = y ∈ R ny |2 ≤ q r 0 ≤ 25, T r 0 (h) ≤ T r 0 ≤ 75, T s j (h) ≤ T s j ≤ 85, i ∈ N,(11)where T r 0 and T s j are time-varying lower temperature bounds, e.g., being higher during the day and lower at night, consistently with the daily trend of the thermal demand [27].",
    "Note that the output constraints are 'softened' with slack variables that are penalised in the cost to ensure feasibility in the presence of model errors.",
    "Finally, for the MHE-based observer (8), the selected horizon is Ĥ = 50 and the weight matrices are identity matrices of appropriate dimension.Four strategies are compared for selecting the weights λ [i] (h) for h = k,..., k + H -1 in the MPC controller:• AV: the average of the ensemble outputs is applied, i.e., λ [i] (h) = 1/n, for i = 1,..., n.• LS: the weights are optimized in a least-squares sense with respect to the last 100 time steps of observations, i.e., {λ [i] (h)} i∈N = arg min{λ [i] } i∈N k-1 h ′ =k-100 y p (h ′)- i∈N λ [i] g [i] x [i] (h ′), u(h ′) 2.",
    "(13)• MD-1: the weights are fixed over the prediction window to the values computed using the Mahalanobis distance based on the one-step-behind optimal inputs, i.e.,λ [i] (h) = λ [i] MD u(k -1), for i = 1,..., n.(14)• MD-2: the weights are optimised within the MPC as a function of the inputs across the horizon, i.e.,λ [i] (h) = λ [i] MD u(h), for i = 1,..., n.(15)Finally, as a baseline controller against which to compare the proposed methods, a rule-based (RB) strategy is used.In particular, a constant supply temperature T s 0 = 75 that satisfies all constraints is used, and the storage flow is chosen asq TES (h) =      -7.5 c(h) < 0.125 7.5 c(h) > 0.175 0 otherwise,(16)such that charging and discharging of thermal energy is conducted when power production is cheap and expensive, respectively."
  ]
}